### Slicing and Generating G-code

- Quality / Speed: Choose between better print quality or faster printing. Higher quality takes more time.  
- Print Settings: Adjust layer height, wall thickness, and temperature for good results.  
- Material Selection: Choose filament like PLA or ABS depending on the print.  
- Printer Selection: Select the correct printer settings.  
- Infill: Decide how solid the inside of the print should be.

<img src="https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=1T4XKzy5mF4Y22mNqa3lR1IHMvboZgZvd&sz=w800" alt="Slicing">

---

### Fill Density

Most 3D prints work well with 10–15% infill. Higher infill increases strength but also increases time and material usage. 20% infill was best for my design.

<img src="https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=1kUfuTmUFdTTTs_93X36hMWOECy0URMmo&sz=w800" alt="Infill">

You can preview how your model will print by dragging the slider.

**Then press export G-code.**

<img src="https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=18XEAWcbGoY_65xGfPZCFSaN8uX5ub-9n&sz=w800" alt="G-code Export">

