### Making adjustments during a print

The printing process began at 20% speed to maintain high quality, especially for curved parts. After confirming stability, the speed was increased to 30%. This helped balance quality and printing time, producing a clean final result.

<img src="https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=1bJUmGRrlJmyborSm3pKRaKrnpDpSTsBN&sz=w800" alt="Printing Process">

